      "text": "In their paper entitled 'Why Frege did not plagiarize the Stoics: more on the relationship between Fregean and Stoic logic' (Gabriel et al. 2024) Gottfried Gabriel, Karlheinz Hülser and Dolf Rami provide an extended set of arguments for the purpose of showing that Frege did not plagiarize, and could not have plagiarized, the Stoics via Prantl's long chapter on Stoic logic (Prantl 1855) or at all.",
      "label": "premise"
    },
    "2": {
      "text": "The authors repeatedly - and wrongly - claim that there is a tradition of Stoic logic (and Stoic logical terminology) transmitted continuously from antiquity to the 19th century that was generally known in the 18th and 19th centuries.",
      "label": "claim"
    },
    "3": {
      "text": "In their introduction and passim the authors argue that Frege took the German 19th century philosophical and logical tradition for granted and drew on them without acknowledgement, and that this is not plagiarism",
      "label": "premise"
    },
    "4": {
      "text": "if a theory is generally known and available, then reference to its author is not required",
      "label": "premise"
    },
